Class
Method or Message: method: function scoped in the class
Field or attribute
Object or Instance

class PartyAnimal  
  x = 0    <-- each partyAnimal object has a bit of data, this is a method
  
  def party(self)
  self.x = self.x + 1     <-- each PartyAnimal object has a bit of code
  print("So far", self.x)  
  
an = PartyAnimal()   <-- construct a partyAnimal object and store in an

an.party()   <--- PartyAnimal.party(an), tell the an object to run the party() code within it
an.party()  
